`=SUMIF($I$4:$I$10,"*"&A13&"*",$B$4:$B$10)`

The instruction requires summing values in column B only when the corresponding cell in column I:
 the text from A13 **and** does not contain any numbers. To achieve this with LibreOffice‑compatible formulas, we will replace the SUMIF with a SUMIFS that adds additional “exclude digit” criteria for each digit 0‑9:

```
